starting_post.message: 00:42:559 - Theres like half a syllable here, optional single, same for insane maybe

no major complaints. something i'd recommend is working on emphasis spacing. i noticed sometimes you end up spacing all the sounds equally, instead of spacing them based on how important the sound is (ie. 00:51:642 (2,3,4,5,6,7) - snares, kicks, and high hats are all spaced the same, while having different volumes). 

other times, you space the same sounds very differently for seemingly no musical reason:
- 00:54:468 (5) - cymbal is the same spacing as 00:53:599 (3,4) - while being a much stronger sound
- 00:39:033 (2) - cymbal is slightly overlapped on slider end, resulting in nearly no emphasis

these are just some exapmles.
00:41:119 - optional rice single here to connect the phrases with that subtle hi hat
01:15:014 (3,4) - would unstack these to avoid confusion with 1/4 doubles
00:35:599 - Optional percussion mapping here![](https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/878714666455535667/1145518155314245792/image.png)
Would lower HP to 5. HP 6 just feels a bit harsh for this level of difficulty
03:15:555 - this guitar solo feels the same as every other part of the map. consider making your rhythm choice / spacing a little more unique to fit the section of music
best diffname in the game
02:47:512 (3) - cymbal crash should be mapped actively 02:47:729 here instead of as a slider end
insane tech!!!11!!!!111!1!
02:16:207 (1,2) - the two vocal sounds should definitely be mapped actively. also, there is no sound worth mapping 02:16:642 (2) - here. consider a sound on 02:16:859 to match with snare instead
i will love claris until my very last breath
Uwu
01:37:729 (1,2,3) - you can give this more space because of the kickslider before it. 01:37:512 (3,1) - ends up playing like a 1/2 rhythm anwyay

00:20:598 (20598|0,21143|0,21689|0) - Despite how I feel about scratchjacks on 10K2S, I think these as scratchjacks would play very fun, so I'll suggest that unless your concept for the scratches necessitates these being schlongs
00:56:425 (1) - this could have more spacing because music changes significantly here
01:46:070 (1) - should be 1/4 longer for drum/melody
03:16:946 (2,3,4) - 2 sliders instead to follow vocals + the guitar strums at 03:16:946 - & 03:17:374 - ?
